RollTypeDefinitions.comment: This config file is a (2005 July 24) beta test version for the XML CIS to MIDI converter
Tags are likely to change before final version is stable
W. Trachtman 7/24/05
Tracks MUST be numbered sequentially from left to right on rolls
Tracks must NOT overlap (by setting width values too large)
All units MUST be in inches for the time being
Edge shifting values apply to eRoll conversion files only
Negative edge shift values advance events
Positive edge shift values delay events
By Default, Tracks are mapped to MIDI pitch = track number
MIDI pitch shifting values apply to eRoll conversion files only
ScanImageMIDI files preserve original track/pitch correspondence
REMINDER - XML tags ARE case sensitive
The converter program looks for exact tag matches, including case
The individual track values are only needed to override default values, which apply to all tracks

RollType.Name: Generic_uniform
RollType.comment: Limit allowable punch step sizes to known used values - decimal inches
Default track locations are mapped from X=0 inch origin
Default Track 0 center is 1/2 of center spacing from origin
Assign Channel 0 to Grand Piano instrument # 0
Webbing and TakeupSpool Acceleration values apply to eRoll only
Specific Track Values Are Used to Override Defaults As Needed
By Default, Tracks are mapped to MIDI pitch = track number

RollTypeDefinitions.comment: END of Generic_Uniform Roll Type Setting Definitions
